'''Coddenham''' is a [[village]] and [[civil parish]] in the [[Mid Suffolk]] district of [[Suffolk]] in eastern [[England]]. Located to the north of the [[A14 road (England)|A14 road]], 8 miles north of [[Ipswich]], the parish also includes the hamlet of [[Coddenham Green]]. In 2005 its population was 570.<ref name=population/> Village facilities include a village shop, country club, pub and the community & sports hall.

During the [[Roman Britain|Roman occupation of Britain]], Coddenham was the largest settlement in Suffolk.<ref>[http://www.suffolkchurches.co.uk/coddenham.htm St Mary, Coddenham] Suffolk Churches</ref>

